        "generateUrl": "https://www.juniper.net/documentation/us/en/software/mist/automation-integration/topics/task/create-token-for-rest-api.html",
        "setup": "In the Juniper Mist portal, create either an organization token or a user token. Juniper's docs say to go to `Organization > Admin > Settings`, scroll to **API Token**, and click **Create Token**; see [Create API Tokens](https://www.juniper.net/documentation/us/en/software/mist/automation-integration/topics/task/create-token-for-rest-api.html). The automation guide also notes that an organization token is recommended when sharing access to the Mist MCP server and that Mist APIs are available to customers with a Mist account; see [Juniper Mist Automation Guide](https://www.juniper.net/documentation/us/en/software/mist/automation-integration/automation-integration.pdf)."
      }
